The Chairman of Independent Corrupt Practices and Other Related Offences Commission (ICPC), Professor Bolaji Owasanoyehe, said the introduction of tracking drive for constituencies abandoned projects by his commission has started yielding result as erring contractors have returned to site with a view to complete the projects. He made this known yesterday during a  town hall meeting on “My Constituency, my project” organized in collaboration with National Orientation Agency (NOA), in Birnin Kebbi. Represented by a staff from Sokoto State office, Akibu Garba, Professor Owasanoyehe said his commission had recorded huge successes in recovery of abandoned constituency projects in 12 states. Buhari: N1trn wasted on constituency projects in 10yrs ICPC recovers six tractors, discovers abandoned constituency projects in Bauchi Buhari: N1trn wasted on constituency projects in 10 years